Step 1: retrospective inference regarding the historical existence of the COVID-19 infection at each location, in which a confirmed case had a period of stay prior to diagnosis. The main aim of this step is to estimate the infection date of each confirmed case, given the date of symptom onset. From the infection date, that case had the risk of transmitting pathogens to others. The incubation period of each confirmed case from infection to symptom onset is modelled by following a Weibull distribution44.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
